race.comment: BEL MEZYAAN (2) wasn't far away on debut last start over 1000m at Sandown-Hillside, finishing third and beaten 1.5 lengths by Trapper John, who looks well above average. Only needs to run up to that to be the testing material here. INCONTESTABLE (7) was responsible for a solid effort last time out when second at Geelong over 1140m, beaten a head. That followed a trip to the runner-up stall on debut as well, so doesn't need a lot to go his way to be in the mix again. SWIFT STATEMENT (9) produced a nice effort on debut in better company last start over 1103m at Kyneton when second, so obviously has talent, just has a tricky gate to contend with. XUXA KISS (14) was in the firing line on the corner and finished second last time over 1200m at Cranbourne, beaten 3.5 lengths, which was a sharp improvement on the debut run, so if she progresses from that she can win here. WAVELETS (11) is a 4YO on debut but has jumped out well.
